Manchester United's Patrice Evra Signs Contract Until 2014 at the Earliest

-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 
2011-02-21T11:37:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-21/manchester-united-s-patrice-evra-signs-contract-until-2014-at-the-earliest.html
Manchester United defender   Patrice Evra  signed a contract extension that will keep him 
at the club until at least the end of the 2013-14 season, 
the club said on its website.  “I have won a lot in the last five years, but I want to
win more, and I know that’s the mentality of everyone here,”
Evra was cited as saying.  The French left-back, 29, joined in January 2006 and has
made 226 appearances, scoring three goals, United said. He has
won three Premier League titles, three League Cups and winners’
medals in the Champions League and the Club  World Cup .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Peter-Joseph Hegarty at 
 phegarty@bloomberg.net  